# Test Quick Reply API Endpoints

### 1. Create a new quick reply (POST /api/quick-replies)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Welcome message",
  "content": "Thank you for contacting us! We will respond to your inquiry as soon as possible.",
  "category": "General"
}

###

### 2. Get quick reply list (GET /api/quick-replies)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies?page=1&size=10
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Get quick reply list with search filter
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies?search=Welcome
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Get quick reply list filtered by category
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies?category=General
Accept: application/json

###

### 5. Get single quick reply by ID (GET /api/quick-replies/{id})
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Get non-existent quick reply (should return 404)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies/999999
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Update quick reply (PUT /api/quick-replies/{id})
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated welcome message",
  "content": "Updated content for welcome message",
  "category": "Updated",
  "use_count": 5
}

###

### 8. Update non-existent quick reply (should return 404)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies/999999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This should fail"
}

###

### 9. Delete quick reply (DELETE /api/quick-replies/{id})
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 10. Delete non-existent quick reply (should return 404)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/quick-replies/999999
Accept: application/json

###
